                  <hi rend="largeCaps">WILKINSON</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">BROWN</hi> were further charged with having been before convicted of felony, Wilkinson at this Court on 15th September, 1856, in the name of <persName id="t18650410-name-395">
                     <interp inst="t18650410-name-395" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18650410-name-395" type="surname" value="HILLYER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18650410-name-395" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>Henry Hillyer</persName>, and Brown at Clerkenwell, on 20th January, 1862, in the name of <persName id="t18650410-name-396">
                     <interp inst="t18650410-name-396" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18650410-name-396" type="surname" value="ELLIOTT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18650410-name-396" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>Robert Elliott</persName>, to which</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">BROWN</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">PLEADED GUILTY</hi>, <hi rend="italic">and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">WIL<lb></lb>KINSON</hi>
