                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18650410-name-397" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-397" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-397" type="surname" value="CUTLER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-397" type="given" value="EDWARD ROGER"></interp>EDWARD ROGER CUTLER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a clerk in the Westminster Fire Office, King-street, Covent-garden—I produce a certificate; it refers to a man named Hillyer, otherwise Anderson, convicted at this Court in Sep<lb></lb>tember, 1856, for receiving a 10<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. bank note, and sentenced to 
six years' penal servitude—I believe that to refer to Wilkinson—I was present at the trial—I recognised him at the Sessions—I was a witness in the case on</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="186504100078"></xptr>
               <p>which he was convicted—I have no doubt about him—I saw him and recognised him in Newgate—I believe him to be the man—I have never seen him since till now.</p>
